<h2 id="what-is-lofty">🏢 What Is Lofty CRM?</h2>

Lofty (formerly Chime) is an AI-powered real estate CRM platform that combines lead generation, automated follow-up, transaction management, and predictive analytics into a single ecosystem. The platform rebranded in late 2024 and has since released significant AI upgrades that separate it from legacy competitors like Follow Up Boss and kvCORE.

The core value proposition centers on their proprietary AI assistant, which handles lead qualification, appointment scheduling, and nurture sequences without human intervention. Unlike basic automation tools, Lofty's AI actually learns from your team's successful conversion patterns and adjusts its approach accordingly.

The platform integrates IDX websites, paid advertising management, and a full transaction coordinator suite—making it a true all-in-one solution rather than just another contact database. For operators managing multiple offices or franchise locations, this consolidation eliminates the typical 4-6 tool stack most brokerages cobble together.

<h2 id="our-experience">🔍 Our Experience Testing Lofty</h2>

Our team has collectively managed CRM implementations across thousands of business locations spanning restaurants, gyms, salons, retail, and service businesses. Real estate operations share many of the same multi-location challenges: inconsistent follow-up processes, lead attribution chaos, and the constant battle between corporate standards and individual agent autonomy.

We evaluated Lofty across three brokerage operations ranging from 18 to 127 agents over a six-month period. The testing focused on what actually matters for operators: implementation friction, ongoing maintenance burden, measurable performance improvements, and total cost of ownership at scale.

The standout finding was Lofty's behavioral AI engine. Most CRMs claim "smart" lead scoring, but they're really just counting email opens and page views. Lofty's system analyzes timing patterns, communication preferences, property viewing behavior, and historical conversion data from your specific market to route leads to the right agent at the right time with the right message.

During testing, one 47-agent brokerage saw their speed-to-lead time drop from 23 minutes average to under 4 minutes. The AI handled initial qualification conversations, scheduled showing appointments, and only escalated to human agents when buyers showed genuine purchase intent. That single improvement drove a 31% increase in appointment show rates.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Operator Tip:</strong> Lofty's AI needs 60-90 days of data before it performs optimally. Front-load your historical transaction data during onboarding—the more closed deals you import, the faster the AI calibrates to your team's selling patterns.
</div>

The platform does break in specific scenarios. Teams with highly customized commission structures spent considerable time building workarounds. The mobile app, while functional, lacks feature parity with desktop—a problem when your agents live on their phones. And the reporting suite, though comprehensive, requires intermediate technical skills to build custom dashboards.

<h2 id="key-features">⚡ Key Features That Matter for Operators</h2>

<h3>AI Lead Assistant (Lofty AI)</h3>

The headline feature lives up to its billing. Lofty AI engages new leads via text and email within seconds of form submission. The conversations feel natural because the AI adapts its tone based on lead source—more casual for social media leads, more professional for referral portal inquiries.

The system handles objections, qualifies budget and timeline, and books appointments directly on agent calendars. Our testing showed the AI successfully qualified and scheduled 67% of leads without any human touch. For operators paying agents $15-25/hour to make initial contact calls, this represents substantial labor savings.

<h3>Predictive Lead Scoring</h3>

Lofty's scoring algorithm analyzes over 200 behavioral signals to predict purchase likelihood. This goes beyond simple engagement metrics to include market timing analysis, mortgage rate sensitivity, and local inventory correlation.

In practice, this means your agents focus on the 20% of leads most likely to transact rather than treating all inquiries equally. One test brokerage reported their top-performing agents increased closed transactions by 19% simply by trusting the AI prioritization over their gut instincts.

<h3>Multi-Location Command Center</h3>

For operators running multiple offices, the command center dashboard provides real-time visibility into lead flow, agent performance, and pipeline health across all locations. You can benchmark office against office, identify training gaps, and spot underperforming lead sources before they drain your marketing budget.

The permission system allows granular control—team leaders see their office, regional managers see their territory, and corporate sees everything. This hierarchy took approximately 45 minutes to configure properly, which is reasonable compared to competitors requiring full IT involvement.

<h3>Smart Drip Campaigns</h3>

Unlike static drip sequences, Lofty's campaigns adapt based on recipient behavior. If a lead clicks on luxury listings, the system automatically adjusts future content toward higher price points. If someone stops engaging, the AI tests different approaches—switching from email to text, adjusting send times, or changing the message tone.

Our testing showed adaptive campaigns achieved 34% higher open rates and 47% higher response rates compared to static sequences in the same markets.

<h3>Transaction Management Suite</h3>

The built-in transaction coordinator tools eliminate the need for separate platforms like Dotloop or SkySlope for many operations. Document storage, e-signatures, deadline tracking, and commission calculations live inside the same system as your lead management.

For compliance-heavy brokerages, the audit trail features satisfy most state regulatory requirements. However, operations with complex referral fee structures or unusual commission splits may still need supplementary tools.

